                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> BARTON (WESTCOTE)<!-- recte Steeple Barton: see VCH -->, and SANDFORD, OXON. <persName>
                           <forename>Adam</forename>, the abbot</persName>, 
                  and <orgName key="org_105004">convent of Colchester</orgName> grant to 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, clerk of <placeName role="person" key="place_106046">Berton</placeName>
                        </persName>, 2 parts of the
                  tithes of the lordship of <placeName key="place_106046">Berton</placeName> and of <placeName key="place_106148">Samford</placeName>, with all that pertains
                  to them whether in garbs or small tithes, and in every thing which ought to be tithed, to
                  hold the same with 2 acres and messuages, to farm for 25 years at an annual rent
                  of 30s. sterling, with other conditions if the abbot and monks should visit there.
                     (<origDate when="1200" precision="low">c. 1200</origDate>.) 
                  [Partially mutilated.]
                  </p>
                  </msItem>
